Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.73,0:00:05.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Suppose that one day, I picked\Nup a microphone and said,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.06,0:00:07.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Today, the weather shall be pleasant."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.90,0:00:09.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyone who heard that\Nwould probably think,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.44,0:00:13.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Oreki-{\i1}kun {\i0}just wanted to do a mic test."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.28,0:00:15.24,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Modern Literature Quiz (10 minutes)
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.65,0:00:15.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ten more seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.24,0:00:18.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But maybe someone else might think this...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.99,0:00:18.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,5... 4... 3... 2... 1...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.78,0:00:20.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"He just wants to assert that
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.78,0:00:27.50,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,The correct meaning of 'analogy' is:\Na, metaphor b, comparison
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.54,0:00:22.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the weather will be clear today."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.00,0:00:25.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, time's up. Hand up your papers.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.38,0:00:31.26,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Cause of wildfire determined to be arson
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.79,0:00:31.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Both assumptions may be reasonable.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.26,0:00:34.09,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Fake ¥10,000 bills found
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.84,0:00:34.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The only way to guess which one is right
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.09,0:00:36.59,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,23-member gang of thieves arrested
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.09,0:00:36.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is to rely on luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.59,0:00:40.01,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,News in pictures
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.59,0:00:40.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Things are sure getting out of hand lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.03,0:01:00.87,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You hold your breath to make it through\Nthe bewildering day that confronts you{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.87,0:01:07.04,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You know what this is, don't you?\NWhat do you want to do?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.04,0:01:13.63,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The pain from shrugging\Nit all off as nothing{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.63,0:01:19.55,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}urges you on enough to be encouraging{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.55,0:01:26.19,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Catching hold but making a mess,\Nwe're still inadequate{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.19,0:01:34.11,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}but as long as we can forge\Nour shining, unseen future selves...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.03,0:01:42.62,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Awaken and run where it takes you,\Nleaving mirages behind{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.62,0:01:49.21,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Run with your desire to change,\Nfrom your comfort zone into freedom{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.21,0:01:56.59,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Start choosing between now\Nand the brilliance you can attain{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.59,0:02:04.68,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Unaware of your destination,\Ndeep breaths following shallow ones{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.98,0:02:12.52,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Earth Science Prep Room
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.52,0:02:16.19,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Does Anyone Have Any Idea?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.91,0:02:32.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that I think of it,\Nhow did Sekitani Jun's...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.29,0:02:34.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How did your uncle's funeral end up?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.55,0:02:36.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It went through without a hitch.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.55,0:02:38.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.35,0:02:46.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.14,0:02:48.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing... Just...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.06,0:02:51.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.77,0:02:54.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,if it's okay with you,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.69,0:02:57.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,would you mind lighting an\Nincense stick for my uncle?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.90,0:02:58.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who, me?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.19,0:03:03.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. I was thinking of going\Nto visit my uncle's grave soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.62,0:03:06.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.74,0:03:09.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,if you'd like, you could come with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.25,0:03:13.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.79,0:03:15.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.42,0:03:17.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.88,0:03:21.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, I'll be in touch\Nin the coming days.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.63,0:03:22.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.14,0:03:29.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}, you're always\Nso good at solving riddles,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.10,0:03:33.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,including the one about my uncle.\NI really do think you're amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.11,0:03:38.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't mind it if you say I'm a lucky guy,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.73,0:03:41.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I wish you'd stop making\Nme out to be a big deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.16,0:03:46.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You sure like to keep low-key,\Ndon't you, Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.74,0:03:49.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aw, man, she doesn't get it at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.83,0:03:53.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chitanda, someone long ago\Nsaid something pretty profound.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.79,0:03:54.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.08,0:03:57.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"You can stick a poultice and\Na plausible reason on anything."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.92,0:04:01.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}, the way to say that is,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.59,0:04:02.51,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,poultice
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.59,0:04:04.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"You can stick a {\i1}plaster {\i0}and\Na plausible reason on anything."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.51,0:04:05.72,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,plaster
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.18,0:04:04.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.93,0:04:07.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is {\i1}that {\i0}how it went?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.93,0:04:11.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyhow, I'm saying that you can\Ncome up with a reason for anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.39,0:04:14.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Very well. Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0},\Nlet's say that the reason
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.40,0:04:16.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,why you have solved\Nso many cases so far
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.19,0:04:20.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,isn't because you are talented,\Nbut because you are lucky.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.44,0:04:22.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, don't you think being\Nable to base guesses on leads,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.86,0:04:25.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and then being able to follow\Nthem to make deductions
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.45,0:04:28.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is itself a kind of talent?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.49,0:04:30.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you saying I'm a master of reasoning?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.74,0:04:31.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Am I wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.75,0:04:33.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.41,0:04:37.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know myself how I arrive\Nat the deductions that I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.54,0:04:44.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's probably because you've\Nnever taken a good look at yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.30,0:04:48.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, she is right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.60,0:04:55.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, Chitanda, go ahead\Nand come up with some situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.44,0:04:59.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll prove that I can come up with\Na reason for it, whatever it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.19,0:05:01.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That sounds like fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.61,0:05:04.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm, this is the perfect opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.99,0:05:07.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll show her that she\Ncan't depend on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.49,0:05:10.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, what should I choose?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.12,0:05:18.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyone who was shopping at\NKobundo, near the train station
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.54,0:05:21.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,on October 31st, report to Shibazaki\Nin the faculty room at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.63,0:05:28.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What could that be about?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.39,0:05:29.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Beats me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.10,0:05:33.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's make it that announcement!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.48,0:05:39.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please deduce for what reason that\Nannouncement just now was made!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.48,0:05:41.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm, okay, fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.73,0:05:43.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I accept.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.95,0:05:49.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.45,0:05:57.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your powers of recollection\Nare as intimidating as ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.33,0:05:58.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That wasn't a compliment.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.50,0:06:00.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.67,0:06:04.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Anyone who was shopping at\NKobundo, near the train station
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.88,0:06:09.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,on October 31st, report to Shibazaki\Nin the faculty room at once."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.51,0:06:12.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First comes our word check.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.35,0:06:15.35,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Kobundo
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.18,0:06:15.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,NDo you know what "Kobundo" is?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.72,0:06:19.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. It's a small stationery store\Nacross from the train station.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.02,0:06:19.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.44,0:06:24.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a store run by an elderly couple.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.27,0:06:24.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kamiyama Station\NKobundo
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.44,0:06:26.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've only been to it once.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.98,0:06:29.86,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Kobundo
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.61,0:06:27.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of a store is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.95,0:06:29.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just a regular store.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.45,0:06:32.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,North Elementary School is nearby,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.62,0:06:36.33,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,North Elementary School
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.62,0:06:36.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so I think that they stock items\Nthat grade-schoolers use.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.33,0:06:39.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So it's not a place where high-schoolers\Nwould go out of their way to go?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.21,0:06:41.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose you could say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.83,0:06:42.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.25,0:06:44.38,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Shibazaki
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.75,0:06:44.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is Shibazaki a faculty member?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.80,0:06:48.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shibazaki-{\i1}sensei {\i0}is the vice principal.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.67,0:06:51.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}, you sure are bad at\Nremembering names, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.18,0:06:53.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Leave me alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.39,0:06:59.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"If I don't have to do\Nsomething, I don't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.10,0:07:03.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I have to do something, I do it quickly"\Nwas my unshakeable creed,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.57,0:07:07.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but this was an important contest.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.07,0:07:09.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to have to turn up\Nthe heat a little and go at this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.03,0:07:11.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First off...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.91,0:07:12.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.95,0:07:15.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know why Shibazaki would\Nbe calling a student out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.99,0:07:19.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. I know why that is, myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.29,0:07:23.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's call the student called out, "X."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.13,0:07:29.01,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Student X
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.13,0:07:29.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now we're getting into the swing of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.38,0:07:30.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.55,0:07:32.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.60,0:07:37.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you take a seat?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.35,0:07:37.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.90,0:07:47.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At this point, we don't know if
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.78,0:07:49.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At this point, we don't know if
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.78,0:07:49.90,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Multiple or single?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.19,0:07:51.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Student X is multiple or single.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.66,0:07:57.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shibazaki could be trying to impart
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.33,0:08:00.70,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Shibazaki
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.33,0:08:00.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,educational guidance to X.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.70,0:08:03.37,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Student X
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.04,0:08:04.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Put simply, he\Ncould be chewing someone out.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.63,0:08:06.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you think that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.46,0:08:09.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because when a student is called\Ndown to the faculty room,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.34,0:08:11.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it isn't for anything good.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.76,0:08:13.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That's {\i0}inductive reasoning.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.55,0:08:15.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.76,0:08:18.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}, are you taking this seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.26,0:08:21.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't been this serious\Nsince I started school here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.06,0:08:24.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's even possible that this is the\Nmost serious I've been in my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.77,0:08:25.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.90,0:08:27.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, if this was calling\Nthem in to praise them,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.19,0:08:31.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he wouldn't use a vague,\Nneutral phrase like,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.36,0:08:34.74,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyone who was shopping at Kobundo,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.36,0:08:34.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he would say it straight.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.70,0:08:36.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With a page like that one,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.74,0:08:36.66,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Faculty Room
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.66,0:08:38.62,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,What's this about?\NThe Faculty Room?\NThe vice\Nprincipal?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.66,0:08:38.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,anyone who was involved would be so anxious,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.62,0:08:39.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they wouldn't come down.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.62,0:08:41.45,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it a trap?\NDid I draw attention?\NWhat happened?\NWhy?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.62,0:08:41.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That could be true.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.70,0:08:44.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's more, this page\Nwas an urgent one.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.37,0:08:45.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because he said "at once," right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.92,0:08:49.50,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,at once
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.92,0:08:49.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, most pages say\N"at once." It's not that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.00,0:08:53.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This announcement deviates\Nfrom the standard pattern,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.17,0:08:55.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so we can tell that\Nit was done in haste.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.09,0:08:56.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Standard pattern?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.30,0:09:00.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's say you were making an\Nannouncement addressing me,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.43,0:09:03.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,asking me to come to Class 1-A.\NWhat would you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.02,0:09:06.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see... Probably something like this:
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.23,0:09:10.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Oreki Hotaro-{\i1}san {\i0}of Class 1-B,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.02,0:09:13.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,please report to Chitanda Eru\Nin the Class 1-A classroom."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.45,0:09:18.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that all? Try to remember other\Nannouncements you've heard.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.16,0:09:22.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it were me, I would say,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.12,0:09:24.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Chitanda Eru of Class 1-A,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.91,0:09:28.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,report to Oreki Hotaro\Nin the Class 1-B classroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.92,0:09:32.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Repeat, Chitanda Eru of Class 1-A,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.92,0:09:36.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,report to Oreki Hotaro\Nin the Class 1-B classroom."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.63,0:09:39.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not just school announcements;
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.39,0:09:42.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,these kinds of announcements\Nare usually repeated twice.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.85,0:09:46.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But he only said this announcement once.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.35,0:09:49.48,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Shibazaki... In a rush
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.81,0:09:49.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can conclude\Nthat he was in that much of a rush.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.15,0:09:50.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.27,0:09:54.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And not just a run-of-the-mill\Nrush, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.69,0:09:56.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.57,0:10:00.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For the reason that the announcement\Nwas made after school.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.91,0:10:05.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm, Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}, please don't\Nomit how you arrived at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.54,0:10:08.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Omit." Music to my ears.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.46,0:10:10.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,O-re-ki-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.09,0:10:15.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, right? Making the\Nannouncement the next morning
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.34,0:10:16.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,would be far more effective.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.67,0:10:19.80,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Classtime
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.68,0:10:20.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, Kamiyama High School\Nmay be busy with club activities,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.80,0:10:25.89,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,After school
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.64,0:10:23.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but there are plenty who\Nleave for home right away, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.60,0:10:25.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even so, he made an\Nafter-school announcement,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.89,0:10:27.02,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Night
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.89,0:10:29.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,because the whole reason for the\Nannouncement came up after school.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.02,0:10:28.39,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Going to school
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.39,0:10:29.69,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Homeroom
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.23,0:10:34.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the reason was urgent enough\Nthat he couldn't wait until tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.19,0:10:37.57,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Student X
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.61,0:10:37.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Meaning that Shibazaki made the\Nannouncement on the possibility
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.57,0:10:39.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that X hadn't gone\Nhome from school yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.32,0:10:44.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}, doesn't this have\Nan air of shadiness about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.91,0:10:45.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, it does.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.83,0:10:48.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, what does the\N"shade" in "shadiness" refer to?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.96,0:10:49.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dunno.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.17,0:10:56.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next deduction... whatever Shibazaki\Nwants to speak to X about
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.09,0:10:57.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,cannot be done out in the open.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.01,0:11:01.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whether that's just temporary\Nor in perpetuity, we can't say.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.80,0:11:05.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that because he didn't say\Nwhy he was paging X-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.97,0:11:08.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's that, too, but it comes\Nup even more clearly than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.35,0:11:13.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.11,0:11:16.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shibazaki is the vice principal, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.03,0:11:19.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Coming down on students is done\Nby the guidance counselors.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.03,0:11:23.16,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Student X
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.49,0:11:23.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. Morishita-{\i1}sensei\N{\i0}is always calling students in.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.57,0:11:25.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where is the guidance counselor's office?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.83,0:11:27.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The second floor of the main building.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.79,0:11:30.91,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Guidance Counselor's Office
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.20,0:11:32.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But X was paged to the faculty room\Nby Vice Principal Shibazaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.50,0:11:34.79,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Faculty Room
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.08,0:11:36.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That shows that circumstances\Nare more serious,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.80,0:11:39.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and it also shows that information\Nabout this is being kept
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.26,0:11:40.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,at the administrative level.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.34,0:11:43.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or so it could be argued.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.56,0:11:49.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.35,0:11:50.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.64,0:11:53.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Going by what you've\Ndeduced up to this point,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.40,0:11:58.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it strikes me that X-{\i1}san {\i0}is\Ninvolved in something bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.28,0:12:00.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that is what it would mean, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.15,0:12:02.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.82,0:12:06.28,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Student X
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.41,0:12:06.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,X is...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.20,0:12:09.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,involved in some kind of crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.12,0:12:14.00,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Earth Science Prep Room
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.00,0:12:17.00,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Soukou {\i0}('Frostfall')\NWhen the dew formeth in gray coldness,\Nand descendeth as frost.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.09,0:12:17.00,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Hyouka
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.38,0:12:24.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoo... This is a game\Nbetween Chitanda and me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.18,0:12:26.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no need for it to be the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.10,0:12:29.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, the whole point when\Nwe started this was to prove
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.01,0:12:32.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that it isn't so simple for my\Ndeductions to match the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.73,0:12:34.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, then, this crime could be...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.15,0:12:36.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Before we get into that,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.61,0:12:39.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,assuming that all of my\Ndeductions so far are correct,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.69,0:12:41.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the school currently\Nhas no police officer,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.90,0:12:45.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so it's highly possible that an\Nequivalent authority is here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.28,0:12:49.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If a crime was committed, it was\Nprobably on October 31st here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.83,0:12:51.08,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Incident occurs
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.08,0:12:52.20,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Today
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.08,0:12:53.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And yet, the announcement\Ncame today, moments ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.58,0:12:56.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and was carried out in a rushed manner.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.92,0:12:56.63,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Incident occurs\NAnnouncement
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.29,0:12:58.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,conceivable that immediately preceding,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.17,0:13:00.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a request was made by law enforcement.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.67,0:13:04.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that request could have\Nbeen made over the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.93,0:13:08.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That may be true, but if\Nit became necessary,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.76,0:13:11.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,law enforcement would have\Nto take X into custody.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.10,0:13:13.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If that's the case, it would be\Nbetter to come here directly.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.23,0:13:21.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Custody...? Could X-{\i1}san {\i0}have\Nbeen paged as the culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.07,0:13:22.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.70,0:13:26.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, this is a game.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.32,0:13:29.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right. That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.87,0:13:33.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If they weren't the culprit,\NShibazaki wouldn't have been rushed,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.50,0:13:36.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and could have made the announcement\Nin his own good time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.00,0:13:36.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That follows.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.79,0:13:41.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, as to just what kind of crime\NX could have committed...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.42,0:13:43.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chitanda, do you have any ideas?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.05,0:13:47.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, let's see...\NFirst off, there's shoplifting.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.59,0:13:48.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mm-hm.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.34,0:13:51.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Beyond that, it's conceivable\Nthat while tracking down someone
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.10,0:13:53.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who had committed crimes\Nat other locations,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.64,0:13:56.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they received testimony that\Nsomeone of their description
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.27,0:13:57.52,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Witness
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.27,0:13:59.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was shopping at Kobundo.\NIf that's the case,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.48,0:14:01.02,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Larceny
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.48,0:14:04.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there are any number\Nof crimes this could be about.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.61,0:14:02.65,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Assault
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.23,0:14:07.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Interesting, for being such\Na quick answer. However,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.03,0:14:08.66,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Shoplifting
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.03,0:14:10.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,shoplifting aside,\NI doubt there was any testimony.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.37,0:14:12.16,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Shoplifting
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.20,0:14:12.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.74,0:14:16.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If law enforcement knew what X's\Nappearance or characteristics were,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.41,0:14:19.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they would have probably\Ntold Shibazaki, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.33,0:14:24.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He wouldn't use the indirect\N"anyone who was shopping at Kobundo."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.55,0:14:25.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.09,0:14:28.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The incident occurred at Kobundo,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.38,0:14:27.84,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Kobundo
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.34,0:14:32.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and we can assume that the action\NX ostensibly took was shopping there.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.51,0:14:32.76,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Shopping
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.73,0:14:40.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was the announcement meant to\Nencourage them to turn themselves in?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.19,0:14:42.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It would be weird if that were the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.69,0:14:44.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Speculation:
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.44,0:14:49.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Law enforcement doesn't know\Nwhat sort of person X is.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.03,0:14:52.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, by making an announcement,\Nthey think they will come to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.20,0:14:53.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would that be?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.83,0:14:57.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I had done something wrong,\Nand that announcement came along...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.25,0:15:05.38,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Modern Literature Quiz (10 minutes)
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.21,0:15:04.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyone who was shopping at\NKobundo, near the train station,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.04,0:15:08.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,on October 31st, report to Shibazaki\Nin the faculty room at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.01,0:15:09.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ten more seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.59,0:15:14.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, goody. The authorities still\Ndon't know I'm the one who did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.76,0:15:19.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If this goes right, I could get\Naway with this free and clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.56,0:15:21.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.15,0:15:24.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Under what circumstances would\Nthey willingly come forward
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.27,0:15:25.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,after hearing that announcement?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.19,0:15:28.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If they felt guilty about\Ntheir crime, maybe?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.24,0:15:30.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, if that were it, they'd turn\Nthemselves in, end of statement.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.61,0:15:32.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Today's announcement would\Nhave never happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.83,0:15:35.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.41,0:15:39.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.75,0:15:41.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.54,0:15:44.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's set aside the nature of\NX's crime for the moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.84,0:15:47.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But X felt guilty about what they did.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.42,0:15:51.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They made an apology\Nto Kobundo. In writing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.13,0:15:53.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In writing?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.59,0:15:56.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chitanda, what is today's date?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.76,0:15:58.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,November 1st.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.89,0:16:02.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So October 31st was yesterday, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.85,0:16:04.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't Shibazaki say,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.23,0:16:07.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Kobundo next to the train\Nstation {\i1}yesterday{\i0}"?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.07,0:16:07.86,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,yesterday
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.19,0:16:11.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you mention it,\Nthat is indeed unusual.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.32,0:16:15.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When would you say "October 31st"\Ninstead of "yesterday"?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.53,0:16:19.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When you have a form or a note\Nin front of you that says "October 31st"
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.91,0:16:22.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and you're reading directly from it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.46,0:16:24.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A form or a note, you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.12,0:16:24.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.13,0:16:29.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why does law enforcement know\Nthat X is involved in a crime,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.30,0:16:31.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but doesn't know what they look like?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.51,0:16:34.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would they think that X would\Ncome forward if they paged them?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.76,0:16:38.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Put another way, why do they think\NX feels guilty about their crime?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.89,0:16:41.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's because X sent an\Napology letter to Kobundo.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.48,0:16:44.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It probably went something like this:
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.85,0:16:44.98,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Dear Kobundo:
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.98,0:16:49.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I am awfully sorry. I was\Nshopping on October 31st,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.61,0:16:53.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,when I committed an unlawful act.\NI will pay for the damage I did,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.40,0:16:55.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so please accept such-and-such."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.20,0:16:59.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kobundo takes that apology\Nletter to the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.83,0:17:03.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Either the police or other law\Nenforcement follows up on the letter,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.91,0:17:06.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and comes to Kamiyama High School.\NThat was moments ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.88,0:17:11.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shibazaki reads it, is taken aback,\Nand while skimming the letter,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.01,0:17:13.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,rushes to make a schoolwide announcement.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.30,0:17:15.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just a moment! Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}, in your thinking,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.55,0:17:16.76,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Guilt\NRecompense
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.55,0:17:18.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,while X-{\i1}san {\i0}wanted to apologize to Kobundo,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.76,0:17:18.55,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Assent
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.55,0:17:19.56,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Amicable settlement
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.55,0:17:21.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they were hoping not to get into trouble
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.76,0:17:20.51,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn oneself in
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.51,0:17:22.52,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Arrest
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.35,0:17:23.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,with the police, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.52,0:17:24.94,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,First offense
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.85,0:17:24.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.94,0:17:27.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, I don't think\NX-{\i1}san {\i0}would have written
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.81,0:17:31.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that they were a student at\NKamiyama High School in their letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.44,0:17:34.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How would the police have\Nknown to come here?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.03,0:17:39.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm. When the Kobundo\Nowners were asked by police
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.95,0:17:41.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,if they had any idea who it was,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.70,0:17:44.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they probably said that it was a\Nstudent at Kamiyama High School.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.83,0:17:46.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They could tell that if X\Nwas wearing a uniform.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.29,0:17:48.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.13,0:17:50.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's more, if X did anything\Nto make them stand out,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.84,0:17:52.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it wouldn't be unusual\Nthat they would remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.05,0:17:54.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something to stand out?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.34,0:17:57.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And {\i1}that {\i0}will be the key\Nthat helps deduce
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.89,0:17:59.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,what the crime that X committed was.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.30,0:18:03.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,X did something to stand out.\NBut that by itself isn't a crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.89,0:18:04.89,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Purchase
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.60,0:18:07.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,X committed a crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.23,0:18:08.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's more, the crime was such
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.90,0:18:08.69,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Guilt
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.69,0:18:11.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that without the apology letter,\Nthey wouldn't have known right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.19,0:18:14.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,X regretted the crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.20,0:18:20.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,X's crime was serious enough that\Nit involved law enforcement at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.70,0:18:24.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever X did, it wasn't\Nas petty as shoplifting.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.79,0:18:25.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, what?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.42,0:18:33.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shopping that stood out...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.09,0:18:37.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shopping that broke the law...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.34,0:18:42.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kobundo is apparently a stationery\Nstore aimed at grade-schoolers,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.72,0:18:45.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so I doubt they'd have\Nanything of great value.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.72,0:18:46.18,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Crime
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.72,0:18:50.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shopping... Shopping... Shopping...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.48,0:18:47.98,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Crime
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.85,0:18:49.35,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Crime
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.73,0:18:52.11,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Fake ¥10,000 bills found
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.36,0:18:52.73,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,23-member gang of thieves arrested
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.00,0:19:09.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoo... For crying out loud.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.79,0:19:10.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For crying out loud?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.25,0:19:12.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,X...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.00,0:19:14.00,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Fake ¥10,000 bills found
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.00,0:19:15.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...passed\Na fake ¥10,000 bill while shopping.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.30,0:19:22.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,B-But... But... But...!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.34,0:19:25.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is too far out of the realm\Nof possibility! It's not realistic!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.85,0:19:27.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is not logical!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.89,0:19:29.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's broken!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.56,0:19:30.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's catastrophic!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.15,0:19:33.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.90,0:19:36.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Calm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.98,0:19:39.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is... a game, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.07,0:19:45.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.75,0:19:53.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you know, there's no need\Nto take it so seriously.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.63,0:19:56.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, but still, it isn't\Npossible, Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.67,0:19:59.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you say it isn't possible?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.92,0:20:01.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What we hear about being\Npassed around lately
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.13,0:20:05.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,are counterfeit ¥10,000 bills.\NOreki-{\i1}san{\i0}, you knew about them,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.97,0:20:07.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so that's why you said that X-{\i1}san{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.72,0:20:09.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,must have used a counterfeit\N¥10,000 bill, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.56,0:20:10.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.23,0:20:15.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But X-{\i1}san {\i0}could not possibly have\Nhad one. Or rather, even if they had,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.56,0:20:17.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they would have had the\Nchance to exchange it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.52,0:20:18.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.94,0:20:23.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}, how do you think that\NX-{\i1}san {\i0}came by their counterfeit bill?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.82,0:20:26.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From an ATM, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.16,0:20:28.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Counterfeit bills that can\Nfool ATMs and banks
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.33,0:20:33.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,don't get around that easily.\NAnd if they were that well-made,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.46,0:20:35.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it would be strange\Nthat X-{\i1}san {\i0}could spot it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.13,0:20:37.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, in change... Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.75,0:20:39.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.05,0:20:43.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. You don't get\N¥10,000 bills as change.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.39,0:20:45.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With the exception of commemorative coins,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.97,0:20:48.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they're the highest denomination\Nof money Japan has.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.72,0:20:51.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know what you're getting at.\NIn other words,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.81,0:20:56.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there's only about one other way\Nhe could have obtained a fake bill.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.81,0:20:57.44,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Bank\NATM\NChange\NSecondhand
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.40,0:20:59.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But even supposing that X's\Nfather had his own business,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.44,0:21:05.70,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Secondhand\NFather (own business)
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.27,0:21:01.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and had a fake bill foisted upon him,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.15,0:21:03.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,if X had received it as\Nan allowance or something,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.49,0:21:07.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they would have been able to tell\Ntheir father that it was a fake bill.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.70,0:21:07.37,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a fake bill
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.66,0:21:11.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. If they had earned\Nit through a part-time job,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.50,0:21:14.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they could have also had\Na chance to exchange it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.00,0:21:14.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.29,0:21:17.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What if they found it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.63,0:21:19.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That would be strange, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.88,0:21:23.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, someone who would pass a\Nfake bill to get some pocket money
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.67,0:21:26.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,wouldn't be too quick to write\Nan apology letter, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.64,0:21:30.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,X probably felt guilty even\Nwhile they were passing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.93,0:21:30.56,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Passed a fake bill?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.56,0:21:33.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Without knowing where they\Nobtained the counterfeit bill,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.39,0:21:36.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it's impossible for your\Ndeduction to be realistic.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.69,0:21:38.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.98,0:21:42.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,¥10,000...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.15,0:21:45.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chitanda, do you like money?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.03,0:21:48.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, let's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.45,0:21:51.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think it's fair to say that\NI like it more than I dislike it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.04,0:21:54.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you dropped ¥10,000 in\Nthe ditch, would you miss it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.46,0:21:59.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think I would. That is, unless\Nthe money wasn't genuine.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.17,0:22:04.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it was your own money,\Nthere's no doubt you'd miss ¥10,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.13,0:22:08.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The reason X felt guilty,\Neven while they were passing it,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.14,0:22:10.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was probably because\Nit was their own money.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.22,0:22:15.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,X must have gotten that bill from\Nsomeone, thinking it was legitimate.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.68,0:22:19.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it wasn't from wages or allowance,\Nthat leaves only one thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.86,0:22:22.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Money they got back\Nfrom loaning it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.52,0:22:25.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If they got their ¥10,000 back,\Nand it turned out to be a fake bill,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.78,0:22:30.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,X would be disappointed. It's hard\Nto blame them for wanting to use it
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.37,0:22:33.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,at a store run by an old man and old lady,\Neven knowing it was wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.04,0:22:38.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even so, X-{\i1}san {\i0}could have\Nsaid it was counterfeit,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.96,0:22:40.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and asked to exchange it!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.08,0:22:43.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really? A counterfeit bill is like\Nthe joker in a game of Old Maid.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.75,0:22:45.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody wants to get stuck with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.80,0:22:49.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, this sounds plenty\Nplausible, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.68,0:22:52.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Hey, X, I've got the money\NI borrowed from you before."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.93,0:22:54.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Ah, Y-{\i1}senpai{\i0}, thank you."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.97,0:22:57.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"It was ¥10,000, right? Here you go."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.06,0:22:59.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Yes, thanks."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.60,0:23:02.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, surprise, it's a fake bill.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.40,0:23:09.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y, who X lent the money to,\Nis in a position higher than X is.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.20,0:23:12.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why, when Y gave them\Na fake bill, they couldn't object.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.16,0:23:16.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At this point, we can say\Nthat X is a single person.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.66,0:23:19.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kobundo being a stationery store\Nthat sells inexpensive items,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.42,0:23:22.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,if a few high-schoolers came in\Nbuying things with ¥10,000 bills,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.84,0:23:24.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that would seem out of place.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.34,0:23:27.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That wraps that up.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.84,0:23:31.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So what about Y?\NY also came by the fake bill.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.39,0:23:35.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It could be that they got it\Nback from a Z above them.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.55,0:23:37.43,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Student X
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.35,0:23:38.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we lump everyone Y and beyond\Nas one collective Y,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.48,0:23:40.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,then who is Y?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.48,0:23:43.48,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Counterfeiter Y
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.10,0:23:42.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A store manager\Nsomewhere without a conscience,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.23,0:23:43.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or the counterfeiter themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.61,0:23:47.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The reason the police might be involved
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.11,0:23:49.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,could be because they anticipate\Nbeing able to find out from X
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.28,0:23:52.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,where the fake bills are coming from.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.70,0:23:54.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And that... is my deduction.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.71,0:24:06.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm, after all that talking I did,\Nnot saying anything back...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.34,0:24:07.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is a bit mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.39,0:24:20.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kobundo is over that way, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.27,0:24:26.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Anyone who was shopping at\NKobundo, near the train station,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.48,0:24:32.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,on October 31st, report to Shibazaki\Nin the faculty room at once."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.20,0:24:37.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When you think about it, we got\Na lot of mileage from just that.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.24,0:24:41.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, we did. End of game.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.25,0:24:45.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.33,0:24:47.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm? What?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.50,0:24:52.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought we started this game\Nso that you could prove something.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.51,0:24:56.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, now that you mention it...\NWhat was it, again?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.18,0:24:57.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.43,0:25:01.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.02,0:25:06.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,would you like to deduce what it was?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.57,0:25:16.03,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Earth Science Prep Room
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.24,0:25:14.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give me a break.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.37,0:25:25.37,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Man in possession of\Ncounterfeit currency arrested
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.79,0:25:29.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ho... I seem to remember\Nthat whole game yesterday
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.42,0:25:33.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was over something that\Ncouldn't possibly be true...?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.23,0:25:56.28,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This situation is an unscientific\Nmontage of emotions{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.91,0:25:59.58,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Who is calling whom?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.58,0:26:05.54,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Your gaze darts away when I turn around\N(I can feel it){\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.54,0:26:07.79,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's unkind to tell me I'm imagining things{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.79,0:26:13.34,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}They say having antennas\Nis a talent, right?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.34,0:26:18.39,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I mean I want to know\N(I mean) (don't you?){\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.39,0:26:25.18,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll turn up the heat on your youth\Nfor you now, while there's time{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.18,0:26:29.86,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If we can solve this tomorrow,\Nwhy not solve it right now?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.86,0:26:35.44,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I want to solve your mystery{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.44,0:26:40.16,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Track down that secretive boyish figure!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.16,0:26:47.71,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}(Today) you are a fantasy,\Ndrawing me to you, no fair!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.71,0:26:53.38,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My curiosity is expanding,\Nlack of tricks notwithstanding{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.38,0:27:00.26,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm fascinated, and I have to know, why?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.56,0:27:09.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, "Mishap-py New Year."
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.94,0:27:11.02,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Mishap-py New Year
